http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Kansas Model Curricular Standards for Health Education

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The Kansas Health Education Standards are to be used to plan and implement K-12 health education in Kansas schools. Although health education is non-assessed in the Kansas Quality Performance Accreditation (QPA) guidelines, it is an important content area. This document provides an outline of recommendations for quality health education instruction for Kansas students.
Health Promotion and Disease Prevention

The student will comprehend concepts related to health promotion and disease prevention as related to: (The ten content areas of health are listed in no particular order. See teacher notes for age-appropriate instruction.)
  1. nutrition
  2. prevention and control of disease
  3. injury prevention and safety
  4. personal health
  5. mental and emotional health
  6. substance use, misuse, abuse, and addiction
  7. environmental health
  8. family life and sexuality
  9. consumer health
  10. community health

describe the relationship between well-being and health-related behaviors in at least six content areas.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: *The starred content listed under Standard 1, are the categories of risk behaviors for adolescents as identified by the Centers for Disease Control (CDC).
